'''Sugiyama Shrine''' (杉山神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Yokohama City|ja|横浜市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Tsuzuki Ward|ja|都筑区|qq=draft|qq=draft}} on a hill at the eastern end of {{ill|Tsuzuki Chuo Park|ja|都筑中央公園|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. It is a former local shrine of {{ill|Chigasaki Village|ja|茅ケ崎 (横浜市)|lt=Chigasaki Village|lt_ja=茅ヶ崎村|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and is considered one of the prominent candidate shrines ({{ill|Engi Shiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳#論社|lt=Ren-sha|lt_ja=論社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) of the only Shikinaisha in Yokohama City from the former {{ill|Musashi Province|ja|武蔵国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Deity ==
* {{ill|Itsutake no Mikoto|ja|五十猛命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref name="kamnavi-chigasaki-sugiyama"/>
* Enshrined Deities ({{ill|Gōshi|ja|合祀|1=co-Enshrinement|2=ja|3=合祀|qq=draft|qq=draft}}): {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kura Inatama no Kami|ja|倉稲魂神|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Susanoo|ja|素戔嗚尊|qq=draft|qq=draft}}<ref name="kamnavi-chigasaki-sugiyama"/><ref>[http://akanedai.net/sugiyama_14.php Sugiyama Shrine (Chigasaki Chuo)] (Akanedai.net)</ref>

Note: On the Kanagawa Prefecture Shrine Agency website, Amaterasu is listed as the deity.<ref>[http://www.kanagawa-jinja.or.jp/search_dtl.php4?jid=170&cd=1202075&scd=&npg=0 Sugiyama Shrine] (Kanagawa Prefecture Shrine Agency)</ref> Additionally, there are historical documents indicating that the original deity was different and that {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was once enshrined.<ref name="kamnavi-chigasaki-sugiyama"/>

== History ==
According to the “Shrine Joint Enshrinement Record Stone” established on October 13, {{ill|1920|ja|1920|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (9th year of the {{ill|Taishō|ja|大正|qq=draft|qq=draft}} era) within the precincts, and the “{{ill|New Compilation of Musashi Fudoki|ja|新編武蔵風土記稿|qq=draft|qq=draft}}”, the shrine was enshrined in Hakuhō 3 ({{ill|674|ja|674|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) by Kibe Katsumaro, the priest of {{ill|Awa Shrine|ja|安房神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, who belonged to the {{ill|Kibe clan|ja|忌部氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of the Kii region ({{ill|Kii Province|ja|紀伊国|lt=Kishu|lt_ja=紀州|qq=draft|qq=draft}} lineage), at Sugiyama Hill in Musashi Province, with the three deities {{ill|Takami-musubi no Mikoto|ja|タカミムスビ|lt=Takami-musubi no Mikoto|lt_ja=高御座巣日太命|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (also known as Takami-musubi no Mikoto), {{ill|Amateruhiwashi no Mikoto|ja|天日鷲神|lt=Amateruhiwashi no Mikoto|lt_ja=天日和志命|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (also known as Amateruhiwashi no Mikoto), and {{ill|Ababetsuhiko no Mikoto|ja|阿八別彦命|lt=Yufutsunushi no Mikoto|lt_ja=由布津主命|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (also known as Yufutsunushi no Mikoto)—which differ from the current deity.<ref name="kamnavi-chigasaki-sugiyama"/>{{sfn|New Compilation of Musashi Fudoki Chigasaki Village Sugiyama Shrine}} The expansion of Kibe Katsumaro's millet cultivation lands is said to have contributed to the spread of the shrine. At that time, {{ill|Tsuzuki District|ja|都筑郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was dominated by the pioneering Kibe clan, and the ancient {{ill|Tokaido (region)|ja|東海道|lt=Tokaido|lt_ja=東海道|qq=draft|qq=draft}} served as a distribution hub for goods. However, due to a lack of additional documentary evidence, the claim that Sugiyama Shrine originated with Kibe Katsumaro is considered to have insufficient basis.<ref>[http://skyimpulse.s26.xrea.com/sugiyama.html Sugiyama Shrine Tour] (In Memory of Kami Yashiro)</ref><ref>[http://www.akanedai.net/sugiyama.php Sugiyama Shrine List] (Akanedai.net)</ref><ref>[http://tytsmed.wordpress.com/2011/10/30/%E6%9D%89%E5%B1%B1%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE/ Sugiyama Shrine] (Tom's Space, October 30, 2011)</ref>

== As one of the Candidate Shrines of the Shikinaisha ==
In the “{{ill|New Compilation of Musashi Fudoki|ja|新編武蔵風土記稿|qq=draft|qq=draft}}”, it is stated, "Surely our shrine must have once been a Shikinaisha,"<ref>{{sfn|New Compilation of Musashi Fudoki Chigasaki Village Sugiyama Shrine}}</ref> and local historian {{ill|Eitaro Tokura|ja|戸倉英太郎|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, in his work “Consideration on Sugiyama Shrine”, also identified this shrine as the Shikinaisha Sugiyama Shrine {{ill|Engi Shiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳#論社|lt=Identified|lt_ja=比定|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>[http://www.okuraken.or.jp/depo/chiikijyouhou/kouhoku_rekishi_bunka/kouhoku52/ History and Culture of Kohoku Ward (Series: Our Town Kohoku, April 2003): Sugiyama Shrine as a prominent candidate] (Okura Mental Culture Research Institute)</ref> Moreover, like many other candidate shrines, this shrine is located on a hill along the {{ill|Tsurumi River|ja|鶴見川|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Water system|ja|水系|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Hayabuchi River|ja|早渕川|qq=draft|qq=draft}}).

== Shrines within the Precincts ==
* {{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}

== Festivals and Annual Events ==
* {{ill|Annual Festival|ja|例大祭|lt=Reidai Festival|lt_ja=例大祭|qq=draft|qq=draft}}: {{ill|October 13|ja|10月13日|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Autumn Festival)

== Sacred Objects ==
According to Higashisato Yoshida's "Gazetteer," the sacred object of the shrine is a 10 cm bronze mirror inscribed with the image of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|lt=Fudō|lt_ja=不動|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref name="kamnavi-chigasaki-sugiyama"/>

== Other ==
The shrine does not have resident priests; instead, it is concurrently administered by {{ill|Tsurugi Shrine|ja|劔神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, which is located in {{ill|Aoba Ward|ja|青葉区 (横浜市)|lt=Aoba|lt_ja=青葉区|qq=draft|qq=draft}}{{ill|Eda-machi|ja|荏田町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref>[http://www.kanagawa-jinja.or.jp/search_dtl.php4?jid=203&cd=1202108&scd=000&npg=0 Tsurugi Shrine] (Kanagawa Prefecture Shrine Agency)</ref>

== Location and Transportation ==
57-18, Chigasaki Chuo, Tsuzuki Ward, Yokohama City, Kanagawa Prefecture
* Approximately a 6‑minute walk from {{ill|Yokohama Municipal Subway Blue Line|ja|横浜市営地下鉄ブルーライン|qq=draft|qq=draft}} at {{ill|Center South Station|ja|センター南駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}}

