== Sacred Objects ==
According to Higashisato Yoshida's "Gazetteer," the sacred object of the shrine is a 10 cm bronze mirror inscribed with the image of {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|lt=Fudō|lt_ja=不動|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fudō Myōō|lt=Fudō Myōō|1=Acala|2=ja|3=不動明王|13=User:Immanuelle/Acala|qq=}}.<ref name="kamnavi-chigasaki-sugiyama"/>

== Other ==
The shrine does not have resident priests; instead, it is concurrently administered by {{ill|Tsurugi Shrine|ja|劔神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsurugi Shrine|qq=}}, which is located in {{ill|Aoba Ward|ja|青葉区 (横浜市)|lt=Aoba|lt_ja=青葉区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Aoba Ward|qq=}}{{ill|Eda-machi|ja|荏田町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eda-machi|qq=}}.<ref>[http://www.kanagawa-jinja.or.jp/search_dtl.php4?jid=203&cd=1202108&scd=000&npg=0 Tsurugi Shrine] (Kanagawa Prefecture Shrine Agency)</ref>

== Location and Transportation ==
57-18, Chigasaki Chuo, Tsuzuki Ward, Yokohama City, Kanagawa Prefecture
* Approximately a 6‑minute walk from {{ill|Yokohama Municipal Subway Blue Line|ja|横浜市営地下鉄ブルーライン|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yokohama Municipal Subway Blue Line|qq=}} at {{ill|Center South Station|ja|センター南駅|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Center South Station|qq=}}

